Welcome to the=C2=A01,169=C2=A0newly Not Boring people=C2=A0who have joined=
 us since last Monday! If you haven=E2=80=99t subscribed, join=C2=A0142,501=
 smart, curious folks by subscribing here:=20
=F0=9F=8E=A7 I=E2=80=99m going to try to record the audio version later tod=
ay, we wrote down to the wire!
Programming Note: We=E2=80=99re due with our second kid any day now. Whenev=
er she comes, I=E2=80=99m taking off for a month. We=E2=80=99ll still have =
some great guest posts and the Weekly Dose of Optimism, but this Thursday, =
if we make it there, will be the last essay I write until September!=20
Today=E2=80=99s Not Boring is brought to you by=E2=80=A6 Masterworks [https=
://substack.com/redirect/902c3dac-a137-4eee-b7cd-81ea04679e11?u=3D16283549]
During my paternity leave, I=E2=80=99m trying to stay as far away from a ke=
yboard, and the markets, as possible.
That=E2=80=99s why I=E2=80=99m happy I=E2=80=99ve been investing with Maste=
rworks. Nobody is panic selling Picassos.
On Masterworks, anyone can easily invest in blue-chip contemporary art, at =
a level that makes sense for their own portfolio. Why art? It's a $2 trilli=
on asset class that's outpaced equities by 3x in the last 25 years, remains=
 relatively insulated from macro shifts, and is actually an inflation hedge=
=2E=C2=A0
Masterworks=E2=80=99 team of experts scours the blue-chip art market, gives=
 members the opportunity to invest in pieces they like, and decides when to=
 sell. Since inception in September 2019, their art investments have genera=
ted 15.3% net annualized appreciation. I don=E2=80=99t need to look at my p=
ortfolio except when I want to admire the art.
The only problem? I=E2=80=99ve wanted to complement my Basquiat and Warhol =
with a Banksy for months. So of course when I finally had a chance 2 days a=
go, the shares sold out in 14 minutes and I missed it. Don=E2=80=99t be lik=
e me. Skip the waitlist with the Not Boring link:
Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B ,
Happy Monday!=20
If you read =E2=80=9Cgovernance=E2=80=9D and thought about skipping today b=
ecause that sounds boring, I implore you to read on. Flipping DAO governanc=
e models is one of the most fascinating rabbit holes I=E2=80=99ve gone down=
 recently. Incentivizing dissent over consensus creates both an internet-na=
tive model for organizing humans and directing resources, and a source of r=
eal differentiation versus incumbents.=20
But like Tokenomics [https://substack.com/redirect/610e5f87-0ac5-4ba1-b0fd-=
659a75e962eb?u=3D16283549], for which we needed to borrow Tina He [https://=
substack.com/redirect/a92546f7-5043-499e-b51b-2fd085f2f70e?u=3D16283549]=E2=
=80=99s brilliance to explain, DAO governance is a topic so complex and fas=
t-evolving that we needed to tap not one, but two, people who live and brea=
the the topic.=20
Today, I=E2=80=99m teaming up with two of my favorite people / writers in w=
eb3:=20
Luca Prosperi [https://substack.com/redirect/6a418be4-0567-466c-a9d4-b6c7fb=
c33753?u=3D16283549], the author of the truly excellent Dirt Roads [https:/=
/substack.com/redirect/00ec5208-2b12-486b-b690-4c3df03d1334?u=3D16283549], =
mathematician, ex-MakerDAO, and advisor to Cherry Ventures.
David Phelps [https://substack.com/redirect/79e1d5b5-4474-4d00-81d7-162bbb9=
c9200?u=3D16283549], the author of Three Quarks [https://substack.com/redir=
ect/077b6ecd-a67d-4606-9504-7de0d0383c88?u=3D16283549], co-creator of ecoda=
o and jokedao, investor at cowfund, advisor to TCG Crypto, Gitcoin steward,=
 and more.=20
Luca and David are two of my favorites because they=E2=80=99re simultaneous=
ly optimistic about web3, vocal about its shortcomings, and actively engage=
d in building solutions. If you don=E2=80=99t already, follow them on Twitt=
er and subscribe to their newsletters to get a sense of what I mean.=20
Bringing old models online isn=E2=80=99t the goal. Creating new ones that w=
eren=E2=80=99t possible offline is.=20
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.=20
Go Fork Yourself [ https://substack.com/redirect/2/eyJlIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
